Makes 8Ingredients:125ml ( cup) cream cheese15ml (1 tbsp) chopped chives15ml (1 tbsp) Tabasco chipotle sauce4 rashers of streaky bacon, sliced in halfMethod:1) Slice the jalape os in half and scoop out the seeds.2) Combine the cream cheese, Tabasco and chopped chives.3) Fill the jalape o halves with the cream cheese mixture.4) Wrap the bacon slices around the filled jalape os, place on a baking tray and bake in a preheated oven at 180 C for 15 minutes, or until the bacon is crisp.